@MovieApi_HostAddress = http://localhost:5102

### GET all movies
GET {{MovieApi_HostAddress}}/api/movies
Accept: application/json

###

### GET all movies with genre filter
GET {{MovieApi_HostAddress}}/api/movies?genre=Drama
Accept: application/json

###

### GET all movies with year filter
GET {{MovieApi_HostAddress}}/api/movies?year=1994
Accept: application/json

###

### GET all movies with actor filter
GET {{MovieApi_HostAddress}}/api/movies?actor=Tom%20Hanks
Accept: application/json

###

### GET all movies with multiple filters
GET {{MovieApi_HostAddress}}/api/movies?genre=Drama&year=1994&actor=Tom%20Hanks
Accept: application/json

###

### GET movie by id
GET {{MovieApi_HostAddress}}/api/movies/1
Accept: application/json

###

### GET movie details by id
GET {{MovieApi_HostAddress}}/api/movies/1/details
Accept: application/json

###

### POST create new movie (fresh title — Shawshank is now seeded and would 400 on the title rule)
POST {{MovieApi_HostAddress}}/api/movies
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "Inception",
  "year": 2010,
  "genreIds": [
    1
  ],
  "duration": 148
}

###

### PUT update movie (MovieUpdateDto = title/year/duration; Genre field removed in Step 23.3)
PUT {{MovieApi_HostAddress}}/api/movies/1
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "Forrest Gump Updated",
  "year": 1994,
  "duration": 142
}

###

### DELETE movie
DELETE {{MovieApi_HostAddress}}/api/movies/2

###

### GET all actors
GET {{MovieApi_HostAddress}}/api/actors
Accept: application/json

###

### GET actor by id
GET {{MovieApi_HostAddress}}/api/actors/1
Accept: application/json

###

### POST create new actor
POST {{MovieApi_HostAddress}}/api/actors
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Tom Hanks",
  "birthYear": 1956
}

###

### PUT update actor
PUT {{MovieApi_HostAddress}}/api/actors/1
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Tom Hanks",
  "birthYear": 1956
}

###

### POST add actor to movie (N:M)
POST {{MovieApi_HostAddress}}/api/movies/1/actors/1

###

### GET reviews for a movie
GET {{MovieApi_HostAddress}}/api/movies/1/reviews
Accept: application/json

###

### POST create review for a movie
POST {{MovieApi_HostAddress}}/api/movies/1/reviews
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "reviewerName": "Jane Doe",
  "comment": "A timeless classic.",
  "rating": 5
}

###

### DELETE review
DELETE {{MovieApi_HostAddress}}/api/reviews/1

###


### Genre filter — expect 4 (Forrest Gump, Shawshank, Lost in Translation, Her)
GET {{MovieApi_HostAddress}}/api/movies?genre=drama
Accept: application/json

###

### Genre filter — expect 2 (Lost in Translation, Groundhog Day)
GET {{MovieApi_HostAddress}}/api/movies?genre=comedy
Accept: application/json

###

### Actor filter (case-insensitive) — expect 2 (Lost in Translation, Groundhog Day)
GET {{MovieApi_HostAddress}}/api/movies?actor=bill%20murray
Accept: application/json

###

### Year filter — expect 2 (Forrest Gump, Shawshank)
GET {{MovieApi_HostAddress}}/api/movies?year=1994
Accept: application/json

###

### Page 2, size 2 — expect movies 3-4; X-Pagination header TotalCount 6, TotalPages 3
GET {{MovieApi_HostAddress}}/api/movies?pageSize=2&page=2
Accept: application/json

###

### Filter + page — expect first 2 of the 4 Drama films; X-Pagination TotalCount 4, TotalPages 2
GET {{MovieApi_HostAddress}}/api/movies?genre=drama&pageSize=2&page=1
Accept: application/json

###

### PageSize clamp — request 110, server caps at 100; expect all 6; X-Pagination PageSize 100
GET {{MovieApi_HostAddress}}/api/movies?pageSize=110
Accept: application/json

###

### duplicate title on create — expect 400 "A movie titled 'Forrest Gump' already exists."
POST {{MovieApi_HostAddress}}/api/movies
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "Forrest Gump",
  "year": 1994,
  "genreIds": [
    1
  ],
  "duration": 142
}

###

### duplicate title is case-insensitive (SQL collation) — expect 400
POST {{MovieApi_HostAddress}}/api/movies
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "forrest gump",
  "year": 1994,
  "genreIds": [
    1
  ],
  "duration": 142
}

###

### fresh title — expect 201 Created
POST {{MovieApi_HostAddress}}/api/movies
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "The Matrix",
  "year": 1999,
  "genreIds": [
    1,
    4
  ],
  "duration": 136
}

###

### PUT keeping the movie's own title — expect 204 (self-exclusion, no false collision)
PUT {{MovieApi_HostAddress}}/api/movies/1
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "Forrest Gump",
  "year": 1994,
  "duration": 142
}

###

### PUT renaming movie 1 to another movie's title ("Her", id 6) — expect 400 duplicate
PUT {{MovieApi_HostAddress}}/api/movies/1
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "Her",
  "year": 1994,
  "duration": 142
}

###

### actor-already-assigned (rule already enforced in Step 19) — run TWICE: 1st 204, 2nd 400
POST {{MovieApi_HostAddress}}/api/movies/1/actors/1

###

### Step 24 — 10-cap on Her (id 6, 2013, seeded 9): run TWICE — 1st = 10th review 201, 2nd = 11th 400
POST {{MovieApi_HostAddress}}/api/movies/6/reviews
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "reviewerName": "Quinn",
  "comment": "Late to this one, still moved.",
  "rating": 4
}

###

### 5-cap on Forrest Gump (id 1, 1994, seeded 2): run 4× — first 3 = 201 (reach 5), 4th = 6th → 400
POST {{MovieApi_HostAddress}}/api/movies/1/reviews
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "reviewerName": "Rex",
  "comment": "Still holds up.",
  "rating": 5
}

###

### Documentary actor cap: add an 11th actor to March of the Penguins (movie 5, has 10) — expect 400
POST {{MovieApi_HostAddress}}/api/movies/5/actors/4

###

### same add on a non-Documentary (Forrest Gump, movie 1) — expect 204 (cap doesn't apply)
POST {{MovieApi_HostAddress}}/api/movies/1/actors/4

###

### PATCH budget on Forrest Gump (movie 1, has Details) — expect 204, only Budget changes
PATCH {{MovieApi_HostAddress}}/api/movies/1
Content-Type: application/json-patch+json

[
  {
    "op": "replace",
    "path": "/budget",
    "value": 500000
  }
]

###

### confirm only Budget changed
GET {{MovieApi_HostAddress}}/api/movies/1/details
Accept: application/json

###

### negative budget — expect 400 "Budget may not be negative."
PATCH {{MovieApi_HostAddress}}/api/movies/1
Content-Type: application/json-patch+json

[
  {
    "op": "replace",
    "path": "/budget",
    "value": -5
  }
]

###

### Documentary budget cap: March of the Penguins (movie 5) over 1,000,000 — expect 400
PATCH {{MovieApi_HostAddress}}/api/movies/5
Content-Type: application/json-patch+json

[
  {
    "op": "replace",
    "path": "/budget",
    "value": 1000001
  }
]

###

### Documentary at the cap (1,000,000) — expect 204 (also creates the missing Details row)
PATCH {{MovieApi_HostAddress}}/api/movies/5
Content-Type: application/json-patch+json

[
  {
    "op": "replace",
    "path": "/budget",
    "value": 1000000
  }
]

###

### patch a movie with no Details yet (Shawshank, movie 2) — expect 204, Details created
PATCH {{MovieApi_HostAddress}}/api/movies/2
Content-Type: application/json-patch+json

[
  {
    "op": "replace",
    "path": "/synopsis",
    "value": "Two imprisoned men bond over years, finding solace and redemption."
  },
  {
    "op": "replace",
    "path": "/language",
    "value": "English"
  }
]

